	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Thursday news bits from Gordon Wrinn</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=213912" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011309.html">Imagine this!</a></B><P>

The fact is, this is all a moot point. I doubt that anyone from Verant/SoE is going to come on here and divulge exact numbers. But the fact is, if it were economically feasible to put more GMs on (and they could find qualified personel), I don't doubt that they would. <P>

Why? Because it would encourage game/brand loyalty. Verant is not trying to just be a one-trick pony; they want to continue to make MMORPGs, and the target audience, in general, are looking for a "dynamic" environment. That's what differentiates it from a single person game.<P>

<B>Very true, and I thank you for the vote of confidence. I can't exactly come post a balance sheet illustrating how everything breaks down, though I will address some of the estimates in Minder's post:<P>

The estimate given for the per-server hardware cost is **far** too low, and there are 34 servers not 23. Furthermore, bandwidth is easily one of our biggest expenses. The "just for fun" number estimated would be mere pocket change compared to the actual number. For overhead, the prices for electricity just nearly tripled in San Diego due to "deregulation". I wouldn't be surprised if our electric bill runs nearly as much as our bandwidth bill. Then there's the matter of the building lease and the lease of office equipment.<P> 

Concerning employment, GMs aren't all that is necessary. There's GMs, Tech Support Reps, Customer Service Reps, and 24x7 operations personnel. Then there's the entire Live team, which is getting quite large.<P> 

That's just the biggest block of expenses associated with operating EQ. There are a number of other expenses and personnel (Sales and Marketing, PR, Legal, Test, Phones, Administrative Staff, etc.) that are also necessary for us to do business.<P>

On top of that there is new development, which is not funded solely by store sales as Minder suggests.<P>

Businesses are not formed with aspirations of stagnation. Regardless of these expenses, we are allowed to turn a profit, and do reinvest back into the business, both for the purpose of improvements to EverQuest and for the development of new products. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011697.html">Abashi, can you do me a small favor?</a></B><P>

Could you give EsterTheTester a small ring and let her know that resistance rates are based on player level NOT spell level? <P>

<B>Actually there are components of both depending on the spell. <P>

Some spells are inherently more or less resistable than others. An example of this is the "Fear" series. The higher levels of the fear series are inherently less resistable. <P>

Concerning caster level, it's not so much the casters level as it is the casters level versus the level of the target. Resistance values receive a modifier based on this difference. </B><P>

If you could let her know this it would really help with her testing of Lullabye for Bards.<P>

<B>The testing is complete, the game designers and programmers have been consulted, and results are in. I'm afraid that the bards will not like those results. We'll announce more later today.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011674.html">A couple questions and comments for Abashi</a></B><P>

1. can you guys make it so when a necro/sk summons a pet in kunark the iksar skaleton shows, this is logical because they are summon creatures from the grave and you know what creatures live/die in kunark?? That's right, Iksar.<P>

<B>It's a nice idea, for those zones that contain the Iksar skeletal model. As this is a wishlist item (e.g. Something that's not needed and has no functional affect), it would be pretty low priority.</B><P>

2. I have one small problem with your logic, you said we keep on spinning when we get stunned because we cannot put any more commands into the server while stunned, then why dont we continue to run when we are stunned?<P>

<B>Running and turning are two different things. I doubt that anyone would want to risk running deeper into a dungeon when stunned, possibly pulling more NPCs. The continued turning makes sense though, since you are being knocked silly :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011663.html">Aystan was HACKED twice! Then suspended from EQ? Brad please help!</a></B><P>

In the interest of keeping the origional post short I will conclude with a plea to get Aystan restored.<P>

<B>He'll have to contact our customer service department at <a href="mailto:eqmail@verant.com">eqmail@verant.com</a> and state his case there. The decision is up to our customer service department.<P>

Personal security of the client system is the responsibility of each EverQuest subscriber. Giving out account info, or loading something on to your system that allows someone to "steal" your login info is ultimately that subscribers responsibility.<P> 

All we can really take into account is that someone, logged in to that account, did something that is considered against the rules.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011651.html">Petition to Reinstate Tweety's player account</a></B><P>

Please give this post a bump if you feel that Tweety should get her player account reinstated. <P>

<B>This person's account status is between them and our customer service department. It's not appropriate subject-matter for the boards, let alone in three separate threads.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011744.html">www.sony.com</a></B><P>

Why did Sony/Verant change the website? It seems slower and is much more confusing. When I hit refresh it kicks me clean back to the homepage. Is it just me or my browser?<P>

<B>I'm not sure. <a href="http://www.sony.com">www.sony.com</a> is controlled by Sony corporate. We're quite far removed from that division.<p>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
